<p><b>Carl Philipp Gottlieb von Clausewitz</b> (<small>IPA</small>:&#160;<span title="Pronunciation in IPA" class="IPA"><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA" title="Wikipedia:IPA">[ˈklaʊzəvɪts]</a></span>) (July 1, 1780<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> – November 16, 1831) was a <a href="/wiki/Prussia" title="Prussia">Prussian</a> soldier, military historian and <a href="/wiki/Military" title="Military">military</a> theorist. He is most famous for his military treatise <i><a href="/wiki/On_War" title="On War">Vom Kriege</a></i>, translated into English as <i>On War</i>.</p>
