<p><a name="Notes" id="Notes"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Carl_von_Clausewitz&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Notes</span></h2>
<p>Regarding personal names: in <a href="/wiki/German_language" title="German language">German</a>, <b><a href="/wiki/Von" title="Von">von</a></b> is a <a href="/wiki/Preposition" title="Preposition" class="mw-redirect">preposition</a> which approximately means <i>of</i> or <i>from</i> and usually denotes some sort of nobility. It is part of the family name or territorial designation, not a first or middle name.</p>
